  "description": "The Kelly Park Compton Crips (KPCC), formerly the Kelly Park Hustler Crips, originated in Kelly Park on the East Side of Compton. Connected to N.W.A — Eazy-E and MC Ren were both members. In 1986, after a cycle of retaliatory murders with the Lueders Park Piru, a task force of 43 police officers raided Kelly Park. A 1986 police substation in Kelly Park that banned gang colors (blue, red, and green for Lime Hood Piru) significantly reduced crime.",
